  <compounddef id="handle_loglog" kind="page">
    <compoundname>handle_loglog</compoundname>
    <title>LOGLOG Log-Log Plot Function</title>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Section: <ref refid="sec_handle_1sec_handle" kindref="member">Handle-Based Graphics</ref> </para><sect1 id="vtkwidgets_vtkxyplotwidget_1Usage">
<title>Usage</title>
<para>This command has the exact same syntax as the <computeroutput>plot</computeroutput> command: <verbatim>  loglog(&lt;data 1&gt;,{linespec 1},&lt;data 2&gt;,{linespec 2}...,properties...)
</verbatim> in fact, it is a simple wrapper around <computeroutput>plot</computeroutput> that sets the x and y axis to have a logarithmic scale. </para></sect1>
<sect1 id="variables_struct_1Example">
<title>Example</title>
<para>Here is an example of a doubly exponential signal plotted first on a linear plot:</para><para><verbatim>--&gt; x = linspace(1,100);
--&gt; y = x;
--&gt; plot(x,y,&apos;r-&apos;);
</verbatim></para><para><image type="html" name="loglog1.png"></image>
 <image type="latex" name="loglog1" width="12cm">loglog1</image>
 and now on a log-log plot</para><para><verbatim>--&gt; loglog(x,y,&apos;r-&apos;);
</verbatim></para><para><image type="html" name="loglog2.png"></image>
 <image type="latex" name="loglog2" width="12cm">loglog2</image>
 </para></sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
